labels.label_value: [Code-server](https://coder.com) is VS Code running on a remote server, accessible through the browser.  - Code on your Chromebook, tablet, and laptop with a consistent dev environment.  - If you have a Windows or Mac workstation, more easily develop for Linux.  - Take advantage of large cloud servers to speed up tests, compilations, downloads, and more.  - Preserve battery life when you're on the go.  - All intensive computation runs on your server.  - You're no longer running excess instances of Chrome.
